Pyszki  is a settlement in the administrative district of Gmina Srokowo, within Kętrzyn County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland, close to the border with the Kaliningrad Oblast of Russia. It lies approximately  south of Srokowo,  north-east of Kętrzyn, and  north-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
